        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Sanctity of Human Life Act</b></p> <p>This bill defines the beginning of human life for purposes of legal and constitutional attributes and privileges of personhood.</p> <p>Specifically, it declares that</p> <ul> <li>the right to life guaranteed by the Constitution is vested in each human and is a person's most fundamental right;</li> <li>each human life begins with fertilization, cloning, or its equivalent; and</li> <li>Congress, each state, the District of Columbia, and each U.S. territory have the authority to protect all human lives. </li> </ul>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
